This paper discusses the decision-making process in software development, which is a core aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). It also emphasizes the importance of human factors and collaboration, which are key topics in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of data to inform decisions, which is relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and programming languages (cs.PL) as these fields often involve the use of data-driven approaches.
